title: For Sale/Trade:  S&W 38/44 Outdoorsman 38 special circa 1954
postcontent:
I'm selling this shooter grade 38/44 Outdoorsman 38 Special revolver. It is pinned and it is a 5-screw gun. This is the N frame, beefy revolver that was the precursor to the 357 magnum.  This revolver locks up tight, shoots accurately and is in good mechanical condition. It also has the original diamond grips that are numbered to the gun.

Unfortunately it has finish issues.  It was stored improperly and grew some rust.  The rust left behind some pitting. The good part is that the inside of the barrel and cylinder were not affected by the rust, so it is purely cosmetic. Mint condition revolvers like this sell for well over $1200 dollars, so you can enjoy this example of fine, hand-fitted Smith & Wesson quality for a fraction of the price.
